
How to install Keras

1- conda activate
2- pip install keras
3- conda install graphviz
4- pip install pydotplus
5- pip install pydot
6- ...\Anaconda3\Library\bin\graphviz ==> COPY
7- Start ==> Edit the system environment variables
   ==> Environment Variables ==> path ==> PASTE

How to install DLib and face-reconition

1- pip install cmake    (cross platform make)
2- pip install opencv-python
3- pip install dlib ==> not recommended
4- pip install face-recognition ==> not recommended
5- https://pypi.org/project/face-recognition/#files 
   ==> download the .whl file and save it to code folder
   ==> C:\Users\Sara\anaconda3\Library ==> PASTE
6- anaconda promt ==> navigate to the address
   ==> cd C:\Users\Sara\anaconda3\Library
7- dir
8- pip install face_recognition-1.3.0-py2.py3-none-any.whl   (f tab to complete the name)

fix DLib error:

1- https://pypi.org/simple/dlib/ ==> dlib-19.8.1-cp36-cp36m-win_amd64.whl
2- Anaconda Navigator ==> Environment  
   ==> update index ==> create ==> select python version (3.6)
   ==> name: python36 ==> new environment is activated
3- python36 ==> click ==> Open Terminal ==> open terminal in the new environment
4- redo all steps in previous part (How to install DLib and face-reconition)

